      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the ISO 10993-4 and ASTM F1841 standard metric for blood pump hemolysis quantification. Relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) is the FDA-accepted criterion for predicate device comparison. Both QoIs directly support the COU decision on worst-case operating conditions."
